Key Match Events: Pete Alonso drilled a go-ahead, three-run homer in the ninth inning against Devin Williams.
Jose Quintana dealt six scoreless innings to keep his team in the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Francisco Lindor commented on Pete Alonso's performance: 'Pete wants to do so much. He wanted to be a part of this. And we kept telling him: you will. You will have your moment. You’ll get your chance.'
